Slide 10: Lecture 10 | What are Tensors?....................................................................................................................
Tensors are the "Containers" of Data:

Scalar: 0D (A single number).

Vector: 1D (A list of numbers).

Matrix: 2D (A table/grid).

Tensor: 3D+ (A cube of data, like an RGB Image).

Slide 11: Lecture 11 | The Python Ecosystem.................................................................................................................
Essential Libraries for your Toolkit:

NumPy: Math & Arrays.

Pandas: The "Excel" of Python.

Scikit-Learn: The Library for ML Algorithms.

Matplotlib: For pretty graphs.
